cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS 

The paper presents a logic calculus that extends linear logic to deal with interferences in proof search. This work is related to the study of logical systems and their applications in computer science, which suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category, as the paper presents a new logic calculus and discusses its properties. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category, as the paper is motivated by lazy evaluation and concurrency, which are relevant topics in programming languages. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category, as the paper proposes a new calculus that could be used to model and reason about complex systems, which is a common goal in machine learning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category, as the paper deals with proof search, which is a fundamental aspect of software verification and testing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper proposes extensions to the calculus that could be used to reason about data structures and algorithms.
